A psalm. A song for dedication of the house. Of David./PR
/PR
I exalt you, /SCG/XXLORIOUS /XXO/XXNE/XX, because you have delivered me; you
gave my enemies no joy on my account./PR
/PR
/SCD/XXEAR /XXO/XXNE/XX, my God, I have cried out to you, and you have made
me whole./PR
/PR
/SCR/XXEDEEMER/XX, you have raised my spirit from the land of no return,
you revived me from among those fallen in a pit./PR
/PR
Sing out to /SCT/XXHE /XXA/XXLMIGHTY/XX, fervent souls, be thankful when you
call GodÚs holiness to mind./PR
/PR
For God is angry for a moment, but shows favor for a lifetime;
though one goes to bed in weeping, one awakes in song./PR
/PR
And I, how I exclaimed in my security: I cannot fail!/PR
/PR
/SCP/XXROTECTOR/XX, when you wished, you raised my mountainÚs
strength, and when you hid your face, I was afraid./PR
/PR
To you, /SCT/XXHE /XXF/XXOUNT OF /XXL/XXIFE/XX, I used to call, and from my
benefactor I sought help unmerited:/PR
/PR
"What use in my bloodÚs waste?/PR
What benefit, my going down into the pit?/PR
Can dust acknowledge you? Can it declare your truth?/PR
/PR
Hear, O /SCH/XXIDDEN /XXO/XXNE/XX, deal graciously with me,/PR
/SCS/XXUPERNAL /XXA/XXDVOCATE/XX, become a help for me!"/PR
/PR
You changed my mourning to an ecstatic dance,/PR
you loosed my sackcloth, and girded me with joy,/PR
/PR
that glory might sing out to you, and not be still!/PR
To you, my God, I always shall give thanks./PR
Psalm 30/XX/PR
